wealth Federation to the newly formed New Democratic Party, which was elected in 1972. Grounded in archival research and oral history, Militant Minority provides a valuable case study of one of the most organized and independent working classes in North America, during a period of ideological tension and unprecedented material advance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aNew LeftzBritish Columbia. 0aWorking classxPolitical activityzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269015840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442690158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442690158.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK